<task id="task_8DDE2C474FDA4B4B86D5C2446EB4461C"> 
  <title>Customize the marketing reports menu</title> 
  <shortdesc>Steps that describe how to customize a marketing reports menu. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog> 
	 <metadata> 
		<othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics"/> 
		<othermeta name="topic" content="Admin tools"/> </metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <taskbody> 
	 <steps id="steps_5EF23FAA3412434E8539C732EF08BD54"> 
		<step id="step_96CB3DD8012E4FB493C76ABEE295ABB5"> 
		  <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Analytics</uicontrol> &gt;<uicontrol>Admin</uicontrol>
			 &gt; 
			 <uicontrol>Report Suites</uicontrol> to open the 
			 <wintitle>Report Suite Manager</wintitle>. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_B2AEB72CBAB64036BE2ED419CFDC13B6"> 
		  <cmd>Select a report suite. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_A326345ED8BE49738A22657FB55ADF8E"> 
		  <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Edit Settings</uicontrol> &gt; 
			 <uicontrol>General</uicontrol> &gt; 
			 <uicontrol>Customize Menus</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_C3F69BB0F64D46E2A57D7BFE058FB597"> 
		  <cmd>Locate a desired menu item. 
		  </cmd> 
		  <stepresult> 
			 <p>You can reorder the menu by dragging items to a new location in
				the menu. 
			 </p> 
			 <p>See 
				<xref
				 href="customize_menus.xml#concept_26EBD206909D4E4EB0F4C14D77C52562"
				 format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Menu Customizing?></xref> for
				descriptions of UI elements. 
			 </p> 
		  </stepresult> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_1215177FADF24014A399006967AD6A9F"> 
		  <cmd>Use the toolbar to modify the menu as desired. 
		  </cmd> 
		  <stepresult> 
			 <p> 
				<note>Based on the currently selected item, some tools can be
				  disabled. 
				</note> 
			 </p> 
		  </stepresult> 
		</step> 
	 </steps> 
  </taskbody> 
</task>
